1 the individual's biological sex.
2 (d) No student shall be subject to any disciplinary action for declining
3 to address an individual using a name other than the name listed on the
4 individual's birth certificate or a pronoun or title that is inconsistent with
5 the individual's biological sex.
6 (e) A person who is harmed by a violation of this section may bring a
7 cause of action for injunctive relief, monetary damages, reasonable
8 attorney fees and any other appropriate relief.
9 (f) As used in this section:
10 (1) "Minor" means an unemancipated individual under 18 years of
11 age.
12 (2) "Parent" means natural parent, adoptive parent or person legally
13 authorized to act on behalf of the child.
14 (3) "Postsecondary educational institution" means the same as
15 defined in K.S.A. 74-3201b, and amendments thereto.
16 (4) "Student" means any unemancipated individual under 18 years of
17 age who is enrolled in and attending a public school or postsecondary
18 educational institution.
19 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
20 publication in the statute book.

